				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One word, 
<br />

<br />
Katta!! MY GOD KATTA!!
<br />

<br />
This was by far the best xp for me i have ever seen.  in a total of 18 hours i went from 44 to 50 solo.  I recamend this to absolutely any mage that wants 49 fast.  Using the 44 Fire pet, zone into katta from the Tenenbrous mountains zone.  U can walk all the way from shadowhaven/paludal if u want, but i usually just got a port to grimling, which is right next to tenenbrous.  Use Caution!, the mobs along the way will eat u!, if ur unsure about the way get a map to be 100% sure u know which way to run if u get in trouble.  Maps are Available at <a href="http://www.eqatlas.com" target="_blank">http://www.eqatlas.com</a> 
<br />

<br />
Anyway, u zone in from tenebrous, get ur 44 fire pet up, if u dont have it, super!, because unless ur a dark race u can buy all the 44 pets in katta in the mage guild near the back.  Get ur fire pet up, give him armor and swords, burnout n such, wait until he casts his damage sheild, then goto town.  As Soon as u zone in from TM, u will see gaurds, Legoinairres.  These are what ur going to be killing. Depending on ur gear / horse n what not, u can kill faster or slower then i did, but still awesome xp either way.  The gaurds are on an 15 - 18 spawn, ( never timed it perfect but its around that)
<br />

<br />
This is what i did, when u get there u should know what im talking about.  U pull the first 2 gaurds near the archway when u zone in with malise or dispell whichever u prefer.  Pulling the left gaurd first will usually get him single, but sometimes the other will add, its random for some reason, as i have experianced this zone to be pretty buggy.  Send pet in, and just chail heal for a bit, and lay in a few nukes.  They go down pretty easy.  Med, and move on.  After the arch way there is a pathway a bit ahead to the left, with 2 more guards.  Pull the closest, and once again sometimes they come single, sometimes they dont.  
<br />

<br />
There is a single pathing gaurd to the right and around the corner of the archway/zonein.  Watch for him he will add if ur already engaged.  After the 2 by the path, move to the right, there will be a large building, u should see a single gaurd standing by the door.  Pull him and nuke/heal pet until done.  Then move to the oposite side of where the previous gaurd was standing, pull the gaurd there and keel.  Facing the building, there is one more gaurd off to the left in corner, he can be easy seen.  
<br />

<br />
Straight out from the archway, past the path to the left, there is another building much like the first, u will pass the green courtyard getting here, so dont go in there, just straight out from the archway.  Pull nuke/heal pet, yummy xp, move to the oposite gaurd on this building, and repeat.  There is also a wanderer here, so watch ur pullz.  Moving around the Large building in the middle with the garden to the right.  u come to 1 large building with 2 of the same gaurds standing watch, pulling is sometimes single sometimes, sometimes not.  After these are done, in the far right corner there are 2 more gaurds. Kill and move on.
<br />

<br />
By about this time, depending how fast ur killing, the gaurds at the zone in should have popped by now. so u can go back and kill them again.  This provides non stop xp 44 - 50, and the lewt is awesome 3-6pp per kill and almost every gaurd drops weapons u can sell for 5pp.  I used fire pet because of his DS, but feel free to mix it up if u wish.  This spot is good until 50, where some start turning light blue. But still by far the best xp i have ever had.  
<br />

<br />
One Final Word of Caution, killing here will make u KoS to Some Mage Guild NPC's Across Norath.  I have been to almost all of them and have only had problems in Felwithe.  This WILL NOT affect any epic quest npcs, so no need to worry about that.  Katta faction can be repaired by hunting in seru, which is also good xp grouped or trio. Good Luck with this Guys, it was a big help to me ^_^
<br />

<br />
Arsin Firestarter
<br />
Epic 55 Mage of Bristlebane
<br />
"Dont Worry, Absor Smash"</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
