				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I tried the spot and have enjoyed good exp there... with one difference.  There is now a little halfling girl--a Katta Citizen--who will come "out of nowhere" and attack you with the speed of a monk...and Boy is she p*ssed!  {I think she has a thing for the guards  :o }  She is very random from what I can tell, and I've encountered her at the archway and in the courtyard area.  First time she stunned me and beat me down within seconds... Second time I made it to the zone to Tenebrous with a few HP's left.  She did not go for my Pet, nor was his attack/taunt successful in gaining her attention.  
<br />

<br />
Second thing I noticed was a Katta Dog type pet who is usually between the Tenebrous zone and the archway.  He cons red to me at 48, but has never attacked, nor have I attacked him.  
<br />

<br />
Third,  I was switching between Echo Caverns and Katta during these last 4 levels, and something showed up that could be a concern to some.  At first my faction, at 44, with all the guards posted in Shadowhaven and Echo were either Indifferent, and here and there some where Apprehensive.  After Katta, and 4 levels, All these guards have dropped, and all are either Dubious, or Apprehensive.   
<br />

<br />
Lastly,  When I first took a look into the Taskmaster's room in Echo I conned the Undead Slaves that surround him.  They were all indifferent to me.  Now they are all Amiable.   I killed them anyway.   :twisted: .  
<br />

<br />
I think there is a possibility that faction with Guards everywhere could be negatively affected....so.... now I will be careful to con guards in any zone where I was previously safe to venture near or past.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for a nice post.
<br />

